==Russian==
[[Category:Russian names]]
===Etymology===
The surname [[Ржевский]] is the adjective of [[Ржев]] ([[Rzhev]]), a small but very old town situated on the [[Volga]] River between [[Moscow]] and [[Minsk]].

===Proper noun===
'''[[поручик]] [[Ржевский]]''' (porúčik Ržévskij) {{m}}

#[[lieutenant]] [[Rzhevsky]]
#:(A fictional young cavalry officer, coarse and vulgar, who appears in numerous popular Russian jokes that poke fun at social sophistication and decorum.)

